  "instructions": [
    "Heat 1 tablespoon of vegetable oil in the ttukbaegi earthenware pot over medium heat.",
    "Add the sliced garlic, galangal, and green chilies, and stir-fry until fragrant.",
    "Add the beef fillet and sear until browned on all sides.",
    "Add the fish sauce, toasted rice powder, palm sugar, and black peppercorns, and stir to combine.",
    "Pour in the coconut milk, and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Reduce the heat to low and cook for 20 minutes, or until the beef is tender and the sauce has thickened.",
    "Season with salt to taste.",
    "Garnish with chopped cilantro and serve hot."
